      "ESSeqNum": 3,
      "FacilityID": 1000032003,
      "SummaryText": " extinguished the fire after approximately 8 minutes.  Braskem then undertook an investigation of the incident, and determined that  the engine of the truck at Rack 15 was the ignition source of the fire, as the engine temperature under unloading conditions exceeded that needed to ignite propylene.  As a result of the investigation, operational procedures for unloading propylene, driver qualification and testing of unloading equipment were revised to provide detailed instruction to Braskem and contract drivers  to govern activities both prior to and during unloading operations.\n\nSimilarly, to the extent that the prior owner of the process operation conducted any relevant evaluation, including a process hazard assessment, with respect to the process, Braskem regards such evaluation as continuing to apply to the process operation, since the equipment and process activities have (for purposes relevant to RMP) been retained in all material respects since the date of Braskem's ownership.  Therefore, in providing within this electronic submittal information responsive to specific inquiries regarding prior dates on which certain relevant events occurred, Braskem identifies, where appropriate, the date of such event even if prior to Braskem's initial ownership to the extent that such event or activity remains relevant for RMP purposes to Braskem's on-going operation of the regulated process.\n\n\n\nEmergency Response Programs\n\nThe facility utilizes a number of monitoring, detection, and suppression systems to prevent, detect, and mitigate fires and releases of hazardous materials.  These include:\n\n- Computerized process control / alarm/ interlock shutdown system.\n\n- Emergency shutdown/kill systems.\n\n- Gas detectors.\n\n- Flame detectors.\n\n- Automatic and manually activated water spray/sprinkler systems\n\n- Fire extinguishers\n\n- Centralized alarm system.\n\n- Fully Trained Emergency Response Team.\n\n- Communications Systems: Radios, Emergency Phones, PA system, Emergency Call Procedur"
